{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"My name is Ryan Lobo,"},{"time":2000,"text":"and I've been involved in the documentary"},{"time":4000,"text":"filmmaking business all over the world for the last 10 years."},{"time":8000,"text":"During the process of making these films"},{"time":10000,"text":"I found myself taking photographs,"},{"time":13000,"text":"often much to the annoyance of the video cameramen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16000,"text":"I found this photography of mine almost compulsive."},{"time":19000,"text":"And at the end of a shoot, I would sometimes feel that"},{"time":22000,"text":"I had photographs that told a better story"},{"time":25000,"text":"than a sometimes-sensational documentary."},{"time":29000,"text":"I felt, when I had my photographs,"},{"time":31000,"text":"that I was holding on to something true,"},{"time":33000,"text":"regardless of agendas or politics."},{"time":36000,"text":"In 2007, I traveled to three war zones."},{"time":40000,"text":"I traveled to Iraq, Afghanistan and Liberia."},{"time":43000,"text":"And over there I experienced"},{"time":45000,"text":"other people's suffering, up close and personal,"},{"time":48000,"text":"immersed myself in some rather intense and emotional stories,"},{"time":52000,"text":"and at times I experienced great fear for my own life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57000,"text":"As always, I would return to Bangalore,"},{"time":59000,"text":"and often to animated discussions at friend's homes,"},{"time":62000,"text":"where we would discuss various issues"},{"time":64000,"text":"while they complained bitterly about the new pub timings,"},{"time":67000,"text":"where a drink often cost more than what they'd paid"},{"time":69000,"text":"their 14-year-old maid."},{"time":71000,"text":"I would feel very isolated during these discussions."},{"time":75000,"text":"But at the same time, I questioned myself"},{"time":78000,"text":"and my own integrity and purpose in storytelling."},{"time":82000,"text":"And I decided that I had compromised,"},{"time":86000,"text":"just like my friends in those discussions,"},{"time":89000,"text":"where we told stories"},{"time":92000,"text":"in contexts we made excuses for,"},{"time":95000,"text":"rather than taking responsibility for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"I won't go into details about what led to a decision I made,"},{"time":106000,"text":"but let's just say it involved alcohol, cigarettes,"},{"time":108000,"text":"other substances and a woman."},{"time":111000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":112000,"text":"I basically decided that it was I,"},{"time":114000,"text":"not the camera or the network,"},{"time":116000,"text":"or anything that lay outside myself,"},{"time":119000,"text":"that was the only instrument in storytelling"},{"time":121000,"text":"truly worth tuning."},{"time":124000,"text":"In my life, when I tried to achieve things"},{"time":127000,"text":"like success or recognition, they eluded me."},{"time":130000,"text":"Paradoxically, when I let go of these objectives,"},{"time":133000,"text":"and worked from a place of compassion and purpose,"},{"time":136000,"text":"looking for excellence, rather than the results of it,"},{"time":140000,"text":"everything arrived on its own, including fulfillment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"Photography transcended culture, including my own."},{"time":148000,"text":"And it is, for me, a language which expressed the intangible,"},{"time":152000,"text":"and gives voice to people and stories without."},{"time":154000,"text":"I invite you into three recent stories of mine,"},{"time":156000,"text":"which are about this way of looking, if you will,"},{"time":159000,"text":"which I believe exemplify the tenets"},{"time":162000,"text":"of what I like to call compassion in storytelling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166000,"text":"In 2007 I went to Liberia,"},{"time":171000,"text":"where a group of my friends and I"},{"time":175000,"text":"did an independent, self-funded film, still in progress,"},{"time":178000,"text":"on a very legendary and brutal war-lord"},{"time":182000,"text":"named General Butt Naked."},{"time":184000,"text":"His real name is Joshua, and he's pictured here in a cell"},{"time":187000,"text":"where he once used to torture and murder people,"},{"time":190000,"text":"including children."},{"time":193000,"text":"Joshua claims to have personally killed"},{"time":195000,"text":"more than 10,000 people during Liberia's civil war."},{"time":199000,"text":"He got his name from fighting stark naked."},{"time":202000,"text":"And he is probably the most prolific mass murderer"},{"time":204000,"text":"alive on Earth today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"This woman witnessed the General murdering her brother."},{"time":212000,"text":"Joshua commanded his child-soldiers to commit unspeakable crimes,"},{"time":215000,"text":"and enforced his command with great brutality."},{"time":218000,"text":"Today many of these children are addicted to drugs like heroin,"},{"time":221000,"text":"and they are destitute, like these young men in the image."},{"time":226000,"text":"How do you live with yourself"},{"time":228000,"text":"if you know you've committed horrific crimes?"},{"time":233000,"text":"Today the General is a baptized Christian evangelist."},{"time":237000,"text":"And he's on a mission."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239000,"text":"We accompanied Joshua, as he walked the Earth,"},{"time":242000,"text":"visiting villages where he had once killed and raped."},{"time":245000,"text":"He seeked forgiveness,"},{"time":247000,"text":"and he claims to endeavor to improve"},{"time":249000,"text":"the lives of his child-soldiers."},{"time":251000,"text":"During this expedition I expected him"},{"time":253000,"text":"to be killed outright, and us as well."},{"time":255000,"text":"But what I saw opened my eyes"},{"time":257000,"text":"to an idea of forgiveness"},{"time":259000,"text":"which I never thought possible."},{"time":262000,"text":"In the midst of incredible poverty and loss,"},{"time":265000,"text":"people who had nothing absolved a man"},{"time":267000,"text":"who had taken everything from them."},{"time":271000,"text":"He begs for forgiveness,"},{"time":273000,"text":"and receives it from the same woman"},{"time":275000,"text":"whose brother he murdered."},{"time":278000,"text":"Senegalese, the young man seated on the wheelchair here,"},{"time":280000,"text":"was once a child soldier, under the General's command,"},{"time":283000,"text":"until he disobeyed orders,"},{"time":285000,"text":"and the General shot off both his legs."},{"time":289000,"text":"He forgives the General in this image."},{"time":292000,"text":"He risked his life as he walked up to people"},{"time":294000,"text":"whose families he'd murdered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297000,"text":"In this photograph a hostile crowd in a slum surrounds him."},{"time":300000,"text":"And Joshua remains silent"},{"time":303000,"text":"as they vented their rage against him."},{"time":307000,"text":"This image, to me, is almost like from a Shakespearean play,"},{"time":309000,"text":"with a man, surrounded by various influences,"},{"time":312000,"text":"desperate to hold on to something true within himself,"},{"time":316000,"text":"in a context of great suffering that he has created himself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320000,"text":"I was intensely moved during all this."},{"time":322000,"text":"But the question is,"},{"time":324000,"text":"does forgiveness and redemption replace justice?"},{"time":328000,"text":"Joshua, in his own words, says that he does not mind"},{"time":330000,"text":"standing trial for his crimes,"},{"time":332000,"text":"and speaks about them from soapboxes across Monrovia,"},{"time":334000,"text":"to an audience that often includes his victims."},{"time":338000,"text":"A very unlikely spokesperson for the idea of"},{"time":340000,"text":"separation of church and state."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343000,"text":"The second story I'm going to tell you about"},{"time":345000,"text":"is about a group of very special fighting women"},{"time":347000,"text":"with rather unique peace-keeping skills."},{"time":350000,"text":"Liberia has been devastated by one of Africa's"},{"time":352000,"text":"bloodiest civil wars,"},{"time":354000,"text":"which has left more than 200,000 people dead,"},{"time":356000,"text":"thousands of women scarred by rape and crime"},{"time":358000,"text":"on a spectacular scale."},{"time":361000,"text":"Liberia is now home"},{"time":363000,"text":"to an all-woman United Nations contingent"},{"time":365000,"text":"of Indian peacekeepers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"These women, many from small towns in India,"},{"time":370000,"text":"help keep the peace, far away from home and family."},{"time":375000,"text":"They use negotiation and tolerance"},{"time":377000,"text":"more often than an armed response."},{"time":379000,"text":"The commander told me that a woman could gauge"},{"time":381000,"text":"a potentially violent situation"},{"time":383000,"text":"much better than men."},{"time":385000,"text":"And that they were definitely capable of diffusing it non-aggressively."},{"time":389000,"text":"This man was very drunk,"},{"time":391000,"text":"and he was very interested in my camera,"},{"time":393000,"text":"until he noticed the women, who handled him"},{"time":395000,"text":"with smiles, and AK-47s at the ready, of course."},{"time":398000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":399000,"text":"This contingent seems to be quite lucky,"},{"time":402000,"text":"and it has not sustained any casualties,"},{"time":404000,"text":"even though dozens of peacekeepers have been killed in Liberia."},{"time":407000,"text":"And yes, all of those people killed were male."},{"time":411000,"text":"Many of the women are married with children,"},{"time":413000,"text":"and they say the hardest part of their deployment"},{"time":416000,"text":"was being kept away from their children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"I accompanied these women on their patrols,"},{"time":421000,"text":"and watched as they walked past men,"},{"time":423000,"text":"many who passed very lewd comments incessantly."},{"time":426000,"text":"And when I asked one of the women about the shock and awe response,"},{"time":428000,"text":"she said, \"Don't worry, same thing back home."},{"time":430000,"text":"We know how to deal with these fellows,\""},{"time":432000,"text":"and ignored them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435000,"text":"In a country ravaged by violence against women,"},{"time":437000,"text":"Indian peacekeepers have inspired many local women"},{"time":440000,"text":"to join the police force."},{"time":442000,"text":"Sometimes, when the war is over and all the film crews have left,"},{"time":445000,"text":"the most inspiring stories are the ones"},{"time":447000,"text":"that float just beneath the radar."},{"time":450000,"text":"I came back to India and nobody was interested in buying the story."},{"time":454000,"text":"And one editor told me that she wasn't interested"},{"time":456000,"text":"in doing what she called \"manual labor stories.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":461000,"text":"In 2007 and 2009 I did stories on the Delhi Fire Service, the DFS,"},{"time":466000,"text":"which, during the summer, is probably the world's most active fire department."},{"time":469000,"text":"They answer more than 5,000 calls in just two months."},{"time":472000,"text":"And all this against incredible logistical odds,"},{"time":475000,"text":"like heat and traffic jams."},{"time":478000,"text":"Something amazing happened during this shoot."},{"time":480000,"text":"Due to a traffic jam, we were late in getting to a slum,"},{"time":483000,"text":"a large slum, which had caught fire."},{"time":486000,"text":"As we neared, angry crowds attacked our trucks"},{"time":489000,"text":"and stoned them, by hundreds of people all over the place."},{"time":492000,"text":"These men were terrified,"},{"time":494000,"text":"as the mob attacked our vehicle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497000,"text":"But nonetheless, despite the hostility,"},{"time":499000,"text":"firefighters left the vehicle and successfully fought the fire."},{"time":503000,"text":"Running the gauntlet through hostile crowds,"},{"time":505000,"text":"and some wearing motorbike helmets to prevent injury."},{"time":508000,"text":"Some of the local people forcibly took away the hoses"},{"time":511000,"text":"from the firemen to put out the fire in their homes."},{"time":514000,"text":"Now, hundreds of homes were destroyed."},{"time":516000,"text":"But the question that lingered in my mind was,"},{"time":520000,"text":"what causes people to destroy fire trucks"},{"time":523000,"text":"headed to their own homes?"},{"time":525000,"text":"Where does such rage come from?"},{"time":528000,"text":"And how are we responsible for this?"},{"time":532000,"text":"45 percent of the 14 million people"},{"time":535000,"text":"who live in Delhi live in unauthorized slums,"},{"time":537000,"text":"which are chronically overcrowded."},{"time":540000,"text":"They lack even the most basic amenities."},{"time":542000,"text":"And this is something that is common to all our big cities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547000,"text":"Back to the DFS. A huge chemical depot caught fire,"},{"time":550000,"text":"thousands of drums filled with petrochemicals"},{"time":553000,"text":"were blazing away and exploding all around us."},{"time":556000,"text":"The heat was so intense, that hoses were used"},{"time":558000,"text":"to cool down firefighters"},{"time":560000,"text":"fighting extremely close to the fire, and with no protective clothing."},{"time":564000,"text":"In India we often love to complain about our government bodies."},{"time":568000,"text":"But over here, the heads of the DFS,"},{"time":570000,"text":"Mr. R.C. Sharman, Mr. A.K. Sharman,"},{"time":572000,"text":"led the firefight with their men."},{"time":575000,"text":"Something wonderful in a country where"},{"time":577000,"text":"manual labor is often looked down upon."},{"time":580000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":584000,"text":"Over the years, my faith in the power of storytelling has been tested."},{"time":588000,"text":"And I've had very serious doubt about its efficacy,"},{"time":591000,"text":"and my own faith in humanity."},{"time":593000,"text":"However, a film we shot still airs on the National Geographic channel."},{"time":597000,"text":"And when it airs I get calls from all the guys I was with"},{"time":601000,"text":"and they tell me that they receive hundreds of calls congratulating them."},{"time":605000,"text":"Some of the firemen told me that they were also inspired"},{"time":607000,"text":"to do better because they were so pleased"},{"time":609000,"text":"to get thank-yous rather than brick bats."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612000,"text":"It seems that this story helped change perceptions about the DFS,"},{"time":616000,"text":"at least in the minds of an audience in part on televisions,"},{"time":619000,"text":"read magazines and whose huts aren't on fire."},{"time":622000,"text":"Sometimes, focusing on what's heroic, beautiful and dignified,"},{"time":627000,"text":"regardless of the context,"},{"time":629000,"text":"can help magnify these intangibles three ways,"},{"time":633000,"text":"in the protagonist of the story, in the audience,"},{"time":637000,"text":"and also in the storyteller."},{"time":639000,"text":"And that's the power of storytelling."},{"time":641000,"text":"Focus on what's dignified, courageous and beautiful,"},{"time":643000,"text":"and it grows. Thank you."},{"time":646000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}